      },
      "date": "2014-02-26 09:03:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhile it would be useful to quiet this error message from the console (I agree it is confusing), my concern is that the root problem is that there IS no local copy.\n\nI thought Mike had fixed the OSD code so that it could make a local copy of the config llog, but the fact that this message is being printed on every mount makes me think it is still broken.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0fe9a9b3da88d3378769536170fc9792fb320f44",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-26 21:30:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNote that I only advocate to quiet this message on a newly-formatted filesystem, not if it is useful to diagnose problems in copying the config llog (as currently seems to be the case).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
